The paper discusses a model and analysis of a distributed graph database, which falls under the category of database systems (cs.DB). The analysis also considers the effects of concurrent updates and faults, which are relevant to distributed computing (cs.DC) and distributed systems (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the potential for corruption in the database, which is a security concern and falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper provides insights for database designers and operators, which is relevant to systems and control (cs.SY).
